                <h1>Auschwitz Concentration Camp: A Historical Overview</h1>
                <p>Auschwitz concentration camp, a symbol of the Holocaust, was established in 1940 by Nazi Germany in occupied Poland. It became the largest Nazi extermination camp, with over a million lives lost. Auschwitz serves as a stark reminder of the atrocities of war and the importance of remembering history to prevent future horrors.</p>
